<xref evaluate="all" from="ROOT" n="sb;4;7352" targOrder="U" to="DITTO" type="reprint from">SB4,7352</xref></head><div lang="grc" part="N" type="edition"><div n="r" part="N" type="textpart"><ab part="N">

    <lb n="1"/>Ἀπολλινᾶρις Ταησίῳ τῇ μητρὶ 

    <lb n="2"/>πολλὰ χαίρειν. 

    <lb n="3"/>πρὸ παντὸς ἔρρωσό μοι <hi rend="diaeresis">ὑ</hi>γιαίνουσα 

    <lb n="4"/>τὸ προσκύνημά σου ποιῶν παρὰ πᾶ-

    <lb n="5"/>σι τοῖς θεοῖς. καὶ ἀπὸ Κυρήνης εὑρὼν 

    <lb n="6"/>τὸν πρὸς σὲ ἐρχόμενον <choice><corr>ἀνάγκην</corr><sic>ανανκην</sic></choice> ἔσχον σοι 

    <lb n="7"/>δηλῶσαι περὶ τῆς σωτηρίας μου· καὶ σύ μοι 

    <lb n="8"/>ταχύτερον δήλωσον περὶ τῆς ἀπροσκοπίας 

    <lb n="9"/>σου καὶ τῆς τῶν ἀδελφῶν μου. καὶ νῦν ἀπὸ 

    <lb n="10"/>Πόρτου σοι δηλῶ, οὔπω γὰρ ἀνέβην <choice><corr>εἰς</corr><sic><hi rend="diaeresis">ι</hi>ς</sic></choice> Ῥώμην 

    <lb n="11"/>καὶ διετάγην. ἐπὰν διαταγῶ καὶ γνῶ <choice><corr>εἰς</corr><sic><hi rend="diaeresis">ι</hi>ς</sic></choice> ποίαν 

    <lb n="12"/><choice><corr>εἶμι</corr><sic><hi rend="diaeresis">ι</hi>μι</sic></choice> εὐθέως σοι δηλῶ, καὶ σὺ δὲ μὴ <choice><corr>ὄκνει</corr><sic>ωκνι</sic></choice> <choice><corr>γρά-

    <lb n="13"/>φειν</corr><sic>γραφιν</sic></choice> περὶ τῆς σωτηρίας σου καὶ τῆς τῶν ἀδελ-

    <lb n="14"/>φῶν μου. ἐὰν δὲ μὴ εὕρῃς τὸν ἐρχόμενον 

    <lb n="15"/>πρὸς ἐμὲ γράψον <choice><corr>Σωκράτει</corr><sic>σωκρατη</sic></choice> καὶ αὐτός μοι 

    <lb n="16"/>διαπέμπεται. ἀσπάζομαι πολλὰ τὰ ἀδέλφια 

    <lb n="17"/>καὶ Ἀπολινᾶριν καὶ τὰ τέκνα αὐτοῦ καὶ <choice><corr>Καλαλᾶ<supplied cert="high" reason="omitted">ν</supplied></corr><sic>καλαλα</sic></choice> 

    <lb n="18"/>καὶ τὰ τέκνα αὐτοῦ καὶ <choice><corr>πάντας</corr><sic>παντες</sic></choice> τούς σε <choice><corr>φιλοῦντας</corr><sic>φιλουντες</sic></choice>. 

    <lb n="19"/>ἀσπάζεταί σε Ἀσκληπιάδης. 

    <lb n="20"/>ἔρρωσό μοι ὑγιαίνουσα. 

    <lb n="21"/><choice><corr>εἰς</corr><sic>ις</sic></choice> Πόρτον παρεγενάμην <supplied cert="high" evidence="parallel" reason="illegible"><hi rend="supraline">Παχὼν <num value="25">κε</num></hi></supplied>. 

    <lb n="22"/><handShift new="m2"/> <choice><corr>γείνωσκε</corr><sic>γεινωσκε</sic></choice> ὅτι <choice><corr>εἰς</corr><sic>ις</sic></choice> Μεισηνοὺς διετάγην, ὕστερον γὰρ ἐπέ-

    <lb n="23"/>γνων. 
</ab></div><div n="v" part="N" type="textpart"><ab part="N">

    <lb n="24"/><handShift new="m1"/> ἀπόδος <choice><corr>εἰς</corr><sic>ις</sic></choice> Καρανίδα <g type="x"/> Ταησίῳ ἀπὸ Ἀπολιναριου 

    <lb n="25"/><g type="x"/> υἱοῦ. </ab></div></div><div n="meta.27100" part="N" type="description"><p><rs cert="high" type="material">Papyrus</rs></p></div><div n="meta.27100" part="N" subtype="textDate" type="commentary"><p><date notAfter="200" notBefore="101" type="textDate">II</date></p></div><div n="meta.27100" part="N" subtype="principalEdition" type="bibliography"><listBibl><bibl subtype="principal" type="publication"><title level="s" type="abbreviated">P.Mich.</title><biblScope type="volume">8</biblScope><biblScope type="numbers">490</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="Trismegistos"><biblScope type="numbers">27100</biblScope></bibl><bibl type="DDbDP"><series>0163</series>; <biblScope type="volume">8</biblScope>; <biblScope type="numbers">490</biblScope></bibl></listBibl><p>Perseus links: <xref evaluate="all" from="ROOT" href="0163;8;490" targOrder="Y" to="DITTO" type="Perseus">Text in Perseus</xref></p></div><div n="meta.27100" part="N" subtype="corrections" type="bibliography"><head>BL-Einträge nach BL-Konkordanz</head><bibl type="BL"><biblScope type="volume">VIII</biblScope>, S. <biblScope type="pages">215</biblScope></bibl></div><div n="meta.27100" part="N" subtype="illustrations" type="bibliography"><p><bibl type="illustration">Class. Phil. XXII, 1927, Plate I nach S. 240</bibl></p></div><div n="meta.27100" part="N" subtype="otherPublications" type="bibliography"><head>Andere Publikation</head><bibl subtype="other" type="publication">SB IV 7352</bibl></div><div n="meta.27100" part="N" subtype="translations" type="bibliography"><head>Übersetzungen</head><listBibl lang="de"><head lang="de">Deutsch:</head><bibl type="translations">B. Palme,</bibl></listBibl><listBibl lang=""><head lang="de">in:</head><bibl type="translations">Festschrift L. Aigner-Foresti (2006), S. 289, Anm. 39.</bibl></listBibl><listBibl lang="en"><head lang="de">Englisch:</head><bibl type="translations">Winter, Life and Letters (1933), S. 40</bibl><bibl type="translations">White, Ancient Lett